ing her. \u201dI didn\u2019t have to say it,\u201d he reportedly replied. \u201cYou said it for me.\u201d7h agoThe TelegraphPrince Andrew makes \u2018unprecedented\u2019 request for evidence in sex abuse case to be kept secretThe Duke of York has made an \u201cunprecedented\u201d request for all witness testimony taken in his sexual abuse case to be kept secret, it has emerged.1d agoMore Stories\n\nTRENDINGABC NewsTruck driver's sentence lowered to 10 years after originally receiving 110 years for fatal crashABC News\u00b73 min readThe New York TimesWhat Do You Think You Should Be Paid?The New York Times\u00b711 min readWashington PostWine bar customer writes expletive on $300 check to protest $6 service chargeWashington Post\u00b74 min readBusiness InsiderThree members of the Saudi hit squad that killed Jamal Khashoggi are living in \u2018seven-star\u2019 villas in government security compound: reportBusiness Insider\u00b73 min readWashington PostAs Florida shatters its record for new coronavirus cases, Democrats ask, 'Where is Ron DeSantis?'Washington Post\u00b77 min read\nPOPULARDoor Dash executive on 400k caught whining about making one delivery to support ground staff: \u2018This wasn\u2019t in my contract\u2019The IndependentExecutive of the Year: Tony Xu, DoorDash CEO and co-founderAmerican City Business JournalsOneAmerica will require Indy employees to be vaccinatedWRTV - Indianapolis ScrippsReport: Ohio's top CEOs making 322 times average employee wageWEWS-Cleveland VideosMillwaukee Beverage Company Will Require Boosters For EmployeesPatchSofology: We spent our Christmas on deckchairsBBCWorcester requiring booster shots for all city employees; return to virtual meetings, capacity limitsWorcester Telegram & GazetteCostco employees treated after freon leak in Hazlet; store reopensApp.com | Asbury Park PressVSU to require booster shots for students and staff by Feb. 1WTVRChina's CanSino says it plans further vaccine deliveries to MexicoReutersHow to Identify a