        "text": "DoorDash to require every employee and executive to make deliveries        HOME    MAIL    NEWS    FINANCE    SPORTS    ENTERTAINMENT    LIFE    SHOPPING    YAHOO PLUS    MORE...     Download the Yahoo News app          Yahoo News  Search query    Sign in   Mail Sign in to view your mail    News   News   US   US   Politics   Politics   World   World   COVID-19   COVID-19   Climate Change   Climate Change  Originals   Originals   The 360The 360 SkullduggerySkullduggery ConspiracylandConspiracyland     Health   Health   Science   Science   Podcasts   Podcasts   Contact Us   Contact Us   Videos   Videos   Autos   Autos  \u2026\u2026 \n\nClose this contentRead full articleYahoo Finance VideoDoorDash to require every employee and executive to make deliveriesDecember 30, 2021, 11:15 AMYahoo Finance Live hosts Brian Sozzi and Julie Hyman react to DoorDash's latest WeDash initiative, which mandates all \u2014 even executives and computer engineers \u2014 to make deliveries for the company.Video TranscriptBRIAN SOZZI: Julie, we've been talking about a story, at least internally, this DoorDash story, a lot of backlash on online really from one worker at DoorDash taking to an internal message board saying that they do not want to go out and make a delivery as is required for the company under a program called WeDash. And the program, it was set up by the company's founders to help people understand what this company actually do-- does and helps probably make it even better moving forward. And the pay for this person that reportedly made these comments, $400,000 a year, what looks to be a program developer.And, Julie, my hot take is very simple and probably not unlike many others out there. Get off your rear. Put down the $500 video game headsets. Put down the $12 green drink and the Snickers bar. Get out of your parents' basement or wherever you might be, that dark room where you're coding. Go out there and make a delivery. Understand the business.You know, I 